Access Bank Plc has unveiled exciting offers to celebrate its customers this Valentine season. The campaign tagged “It’s a Love Thing” is the fourth and will run from February 10 to February 28, 2021. Speaking at the launch of the campaign, Executive Director, Retail Banking, Access Bank Plc, Victor Etuokwu, said the Valentine season gives the bank another opportunity to show love to its customers and reward their loyalty for banking with it. “We are using this opportunity to thank our customers for their commitment to Access Bank. We appreciate our customers as well as non-customers who depend on our services and products to achieve seamless banking transactions and wish everyone a happy valentine’s celebration,” Etuokwu said. Group Head, Consumer Banking, Access Bank Plc, Adaeze Umeh, said the bank had, in the spirit of the love season, created unique and amazing offers to meet the needs of its customers this season. According to her, the bank’s device finance offer allows customers gift their loved ones with new devices for as low as N1,500 per month, by downloading the Quickbucks app to get started. “Customers who perform at least four transactions daily using our mobile app or USSD service *901# will stand a chance to win N1million at the end of February 2021. ‘’We will also offer 20 per cent discount to the first 4,000 customers who subscribe to our XclusivePlus quarterly plan between today and the last day of February 2021. ‘’Our merchant customers are not left out of the fun this season, we will be rewarding them with shopping vouchers when they perform transactions up to N200,000 or more on SwiftPay which is a revolutionary payment platform designed for SMEs who do business on social media,’’ she added. We are offering these and so much more to show how much we appreciate our customers for their consistent patronage. “To join the rewarding train, all you need to do is to dial *901# to open a new account or walk into any Access Bank branch close to you to reactivate your account and start transacting today to enjoy the Valentine Campaign benefits,” Umeh said. She pointed out that Access Bank is the leading retail bank in Nigeria with over 600 branches and more than 40 million customers, noting that the bank offers products and services tailored to suit the lifestyle of every Nigerian irrespective of age and demographic. 